## Personal data / secrets / external services this project reaches

| Data / Service | Access | Sensitivity | Destination | bws secret name | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `<your-vault-path>` | read | high | local only | — | symlinked at install time |
| OpenAI API | transmit | low (embeddings of public notes) | openai.com | `OPENAI_API_KEY` in `<your-bws-project>` | pay-per-call |
| Anthropic API | transmit | low | anthropic.com | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in `<your-bws-project>` | optional |

## Sensitivity scale

- **Low**: public or derived data (e.g. embeddings of public blog posts)
- **Medium**: personal but non-financial (tasks, calendar topics)
- **High**: PII, financial, relationships, health, credentials
- **Critical**: source-of-truth files (vault, keys, contracts) — never lose

## Reversibility

What happens to this data if we uninstall?

- Local files: unchanged (we only read)
- Vendor-side: request deletion at <portal-url>, ~<N> days retention
- Local DB / index: deleted with `rm -rf ~/.<name>/`

## Blast-radius assessment

If this project was compromised (malicious package update, supply chain), what could an attacker exfiltrate?

- The `<your-vault-path>` vault (if read access)
- Contents of OpenAI calls (prompts + embeddings output)
- Anything else in the bws project (if the bws token were stolen — but scoped)

